{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"45a27fa5-2064-4ed4-88f3-4aa183133c4a","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to catch any breaking changes. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dcf2497d-96f0-485b-aca8-7d9e5b9f5691","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":288,"requestId":"7033:1D8045:94A75C:AABE24:69FBEE76"},"id":"d6e7b3b9-906d-442e-86ce-5fdad2be3350","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:44:28.150Z","parentId":"88158a05-8c29-4a93-98f7-1cc6a6364d3c"}
